  "texts": [
    "(2), n lrepresents the nth person in the first group, while n k refers to nth person in the second group.",
    "The variable r takes on a random value between 0 and 1. pop gp1 1,l defines the lth person in the first group, and pop gp1 2,l refers to another person in the first group, also indexed by l. Meanwhile, pop gp2 k refers to the kth individual in the second group.",
    "Compared to individuals in the second group, those in the third group are less fit.",
    "They select shares that are riskier than those held by the second group, but they are comparable to those held by the first group in order to reap larger rewards.",
    "Individuals in the third group, in contrast to those in the second group, utilize both the distinctions in the first group's share values and the distinctions in their own share values when making adjustments."
